wanted%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20fewer%20bills%20than%20in%20California%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20been%20looking%20into%20dental%20work%20in%20Mexico%20because%20the%20cost%20was%20lower%2C%20and%20I%20heard%20there%20was%20a%20better%20quality%20of%20life%20there.%20I%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20Mexico%20in%202020%20but%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20logistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20pandemic%20started%2C%20we%20were%20told%20remote%20work%20would%20be%20mandatory.%20That%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20go%20to%20Mexico%20much%20easier.%20I%20started%20that%20contract%20in%20California%20but%20didn't%20tell%20my%20bosses%20about%20my%20decision%20to%20move%20to%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20moved%20with%20just%20some%20luggage%2C%20set%20up%20my%20life%20and%20workstation%20in%20Canc%C3%BAn%2C%20and%20started%20working%20for%20Meta%20remotely%20from%20Mexico.%20I%20had%20no%20time%20zone%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20living%20was%20incredible%20compared%20to%20California%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20total%20package%20for%20me.%20I%20enjoyed%20beach%20access%2C%20amazing%20food%2C%20the%20amenities%20of%20my%20apartment%20complex%2C%20and%20friendly%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d672f19-4560-40e8-8ef5-50214237ed64%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20new%20lifestyle%20was%20very%20affordable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20easily%20lived%20on%20less%20than%20%241%2C200%20a%20month.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EFor%20the%20first%20year%2C%20I%20lived%20in%20an%20Airbnb%2C%20and%20my%20expenses%20were%20one-third%20to%20one-fifth%20of%20my%20living%20costs%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worried%20at%20first%20about%20having%20an%20issue%20remote%20working%20from%20another%20country%2C%20but%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20got%20there%2C%20I%20connected%20to%20Meta's%20systems.%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20use%20a%20VPN%20for%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%20just%20a%20regular%20WiFi%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20Mexico%2C%20my%20pets%20and%20I%20survived%20two%20hurricanes%2C%20and%20WiFi%20was%20pretty%20good%20both%20times%20%E2%80%94%20I%20didn't%20lose%20any%20data.%20The%20streams%20were%20great%20for%20holding%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2202f76d46-7b05-4013-87ce-8c9c00c3600c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20had%20no%20issues%20working%20remotely%20internationally%2C%20so%20I%20stopped%20worrying%20about%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20still%20in%20Mexico%2C%20I%20got%20a%20second%20contract%20job%20as%20an%20app%20marketing%20manager%20for%20Avalara%2C%20an%20automated%20sales%20tax%20compliance%20software%20company%20for%20businesses.%20I%20used%20a%20family%20member's%20address%20in%20California%20to%20apply%20for%20the%20role%20and%20did%20not%20tell%20Avalara%20I%20lived%20in%20Mexico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20fly%20back%20to%20California%20to%20pick%20up%20a%20company%20laptop%20but%20then%20returned%20to%20Mexico.%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20they%20would've%20fired%20me%20for%20quietly%20working%20from%20another%20country%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20any%20chances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20my%20meetings%20from%20my%20villa%20in%20Mexico%2C%20and%20I%20was%20loving%20life.%20I%20also%20visited%20cities%20near%20Mexico%20City%2C%20such%20as%20Guadalajara%2C%20and%20took%20mini-vacations%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20both%20jobs%20until%20December%202021%2C%20when%20my%20contract%20at%20Meta%20was%20completed.%20Then%2C%20I%20continued%20to%20work%20only%20in%20the%20role%20at%20Avalara.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232225096-f128-48d3-b44b-e9636c443db1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20new%20job%20brought%20me%20back%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202022%2C%20I%20left%20Avalara%20and%20started%20a%20new%20contract%20role%20at%20TikTok.%20That%20October%2C%20TikTok%20ordered%20me%20back%20into%20the%20office%2C%20and%20I%20returned%20to%20California%20to%20regroup.%3