t%3B%20The%20guy%20looked%20at%20Sarah.%20Uncomfortable%2C%20she%20excused%20herself%20from%20the%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20Chinese%20national%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20like%20I'm%20a%20spy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20later%20recounted%20to%20another%20attendee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20comment%20was%20overheard%20by%20Samuel%20Hammond%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Foundation%20for%20American%20Innovation%20and%20an%20AI%20policy%20advisor%20for%20Project%202025.%20He%20posted%20it%20to%20X%2C%20where%20it%20attracted%20millions%20of%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EI%20was%20at%20an%20AI%20thing%20in%20SF%20this%20weekend%20when%20a%20young%20woman%20walked%20up.%20The%20first%20thing%20she%20said%2C%20almost%20verbatim%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20Chinese%20national%20but%20it's%20not%20like%20I'm%20a%20spy%20or%20anything%26quot%3B%20*nervous%20laughter.*%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EI%20asked%20her%20if%20she%20thought%20Xi%20was%20an%20AI%20doomer%20and%20she%20suddenly%20excused%20herself.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1mepDH6LRc%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1mepDH6LRc%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Samuel%20Hammond%20%F0%9F%8C%90%F0%9F%8F%9B%20(%40hamandcheese)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhamandcheese%2Fstatus%2F1861536440988967204%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%2026%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20definitely%20a%20spy%3F%26quot%3B%20read%20one%20reply%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20from%20Beijing%20and%20had%20a%20very%20posh%20accent%2C%26quot%3B%20responded%20Hammond.%20(Sarah%20is%20from%20an%20entirely%20different%20part%20of%20China.)%20Other%20partygoers%20piled%20onto%20the%20speculation.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20glad%20I%20wasn't%20the%20only%20one%20who%20thought%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20said.%20Another%20insisted%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20dismiss%20the%20idea%20that%20she%20was%20CCP%E2%80%A6%20If%20there's%20a%20plausible%20risk%2C%20%26amp%3B%20there%20is%2C%20she%20shouldn't%20be%20allowed%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%2C%20who%20asked%20that%20I%20use%20just%20her%20first%20name%2C%20replied%20on%20X%20to%20clear%20up%20the%20confusion%20about%20why%20she%20left%20the%20conversation%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20cold%20and%20she%20had%20already%20been%20asked%20the%20same%20question%20by%20other%20people%20%E2%80%94%20but%20by%20then%20the%20exchange%20had%20reached%20escape%20velocity%2C%20spilling%20out%20across%20Silicon%20Valley.%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3EEveryone%3C%2Fem%3E%20knows%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20about%20the%20encounter.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20stop%20going%20to%20networking%20events.%20I%20just%20wanted%20this%20thing%20to%20die%20down.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-earths-tech-war-explainer-chips-ai-china-us-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erace%20to%20develop%20advanced%20AI%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20China%20does%20ramps%20up%2C%20a%20new%20Red%20Scare%20has%20taken%20over%20the%20tech%20world.%20I%20spoke%20with%20Chinese%20workers%20and%20entrepreneurs%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20avoid%20professional%2C%20personal%2C%20or%20legal%20repercussions%2C%20and%20found%20that%20Sarah's%20experience%20was%20far%20from%20rare.%20The%20same%20fear%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuspected-china-spy-bases-cuba-growing-near-us-sites-report-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20espionage%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eforced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-back-online-us-shutdown-biden-trump-media-app-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20to%20shut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20now%20pushing%20out%20Chinese-born%20AI%20professionals%20at%20the%20exact%20moment%20that%20American%20AI%20experts%20report%20a%20critical%20talent%20shortage%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EConcerns%20over%20Chinese%20spying%20have%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20since%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20when%20the%20US%20escalated%20its%20efforts%20to%20address%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimf-cyber-attacked-hackers-sony-rsa-lockheed-martin-epsilon-michaels-2011-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20cyberattacks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202018%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20under%20Donald%20Trump%20undertook%20a%20controversial%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjustice-department-china-initiative-trump-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20Initiative%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20aimed%20to%20prevent%20industrial%20espionage%20in%20the%20research%20community%20by%20investigating%20hundreds%20of%20academics%20suspected%20of%20having%20ties%20to%20China.%20It%20found%20only%20a%20few%20cases%20of%20actual%20spying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plurality%20of%20investigations%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2021-12-14%2Fdoj-china-initiative-to-catch-spies-prompts-fbi-misconduct-racism-claims%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2F2021%2F12%2F02%2F1040656%2Fchina-initative-us-justice-department%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMIT%20Technology%20Review%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20in%202021%2C%20involved%20undisclosed%20funding%20and%20affiliations%20to%20Chinese%20institutions%2C%20while%20%26quot%3Bjust%20three%20claim%20that%20secrets%20were%20handed%20over%20to%20Chinese%20agents%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloomberg%20wrote.%20Instead%20of%20catching%20spies%2C%20many%20cases%20just%20indicted%20professors%20for%20bureaucratic%20oversights%20%E2%80%94%20those%20found%20guilty%20claimed%20they%20didn't%20disclose%20their%20funding%20because%20they%20didn't%20think%20they%20had%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20China%20Initiative's%20slipshod%20approach%20upended%20many%20people's%20lives.%20Gang%20Chen%2C%20a%20nanotechnologist%2C%20and%20Anming%20Hu%2C%20a%20physicist%2C%20were%20both%20US-based%20tenured%20professors%20who%20were%20arrested%20by%20the%20FBI%2C%20only%20for%20authorities%20to%20later%20realize%20they%20had%20made%20a%20mistake.%20During%20the%20yearlong%20investigations%2C%20Chen%20was%20barred%20from%20his%20university's%20campus%2C%20and%20Hu%20was%20suspended%20without%20pay%20and%20his%20work%20authorization%20revoked.%20(Though%20both%20were%20later%20reinstated%20to%20their%20positions%2C%20Chen%20said%20he%20would%20no%20longer%20take%20federal%20research%20funding).%20The%20suicide%20of%20the%20neuroscientist%20Jane%20Ying%20Wu%20last%20year%20came%20after%20a%20China%20Initiative%20investigation%20shut%20down%20her%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20escalated%20Trump's%20competitive%20approach%20toward%20China.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchips-act-bill-to-boost-us-chipmaking-competition-with-china-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20CHIPS%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaimed%20to%20bolster%20domestic%20production%20of%20semiconductors%2C%20the%20essential%20hardware%20powering%20AI%2C%20also%20restricted%20US%20investments%2C%20manufacturing%2C%20and%20research%20collaborations%20in%20China.%20Last%20April%2C%20Biden%20signed%20a%20bipartisan%20bill%20ordering%20the%20Chinese%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-bill-explained-politics-tech-platform-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EByteDance%20to%20sell%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20grounds%20of%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20fear%20of%20espionage%20has%20shifted%20to%20Silicon%20Valley.%20In%20June%20last%20year%2C%20AI%20researcher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-openai-researcher-leopold-aschenbrenner-interview-firing-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELeopold%20Aschenbrenner%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20he%20was%20fired%20from%20OpenAI%20for%20sharing%20concerns%20about%20foreign%20espionage%20with%20the%20OpenAI%20board.%20He%20then%20published%20a%20paper-cum-manifesto%20titled%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsituational-awareness.ai%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESituational%20Awareness%3A%20The%20Decade%20Ahead%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20race%20to%20AGI%2C%20or%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20what%20he%20calls%20the%20%26quot%3Bmost%20powerful%20weapon%20mankind%20has%20ever%20created%2C%26quot%3B%20comparable%20to%20nuclear%20weapons.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20lucky%2C%20we'll%20be%20in%20an%20all-out%20race%20with%20the%20CCP%3B%20if%20we're%20unlucky%2C%20an%20all-out%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20In%20a%20section%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Free%20World%20Must%20Prevail%2C%26quot%3B%20Aschenbrenner%20paints%20a%20dystopian%20scenario%20where%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20steals%20model%20weights%20and%20algorithms%20and%20uses%20them%20to%20target%20%26quot%3Badvanced%20bioweapons%26quot%3B%20at%20%26quot%3Banybody%20but%20Han%20Chinese%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bindividually%20assess%20every%20citizen%20for%20dissent%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Benforce%20the%20Party's%20conception%20of%20'truth.'%26quot%3B%20The%20paper%20was%20widely%20circulated%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20even%20shared%20to%20X%20by%20Ivanka%20Trump.%20(OpenAI%20has%20said%20the%20concerns%20Aschenbrenner%20shared%20with%20the%20board%20were%20not%20the%20reason%20he%20was%20fired.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20venture%20capitalist%20Marc%20Andreessen%20entertained%20a%20similar%20thought%20experiment%20last%20March.%20%26quot%3BLet's%20assume%20that%20AI%20in%202024%20is%20like%20atomic%20technology%20in%201943%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20X.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20see%20is%20the%20security%20equivalent%20of%20swiss%20cheese.%20My%20own%20assumption%20is%20that%20all%20such%20American%20AI%20labs%20are%20fully%20penetrated%20and%20that%20China%20is%20getting%20nightly%20downloads%20of%20all%20American%20AI%20research%20and%20code%20RIGHT%20NOW.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20mounting%20concerns%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fc5594136-55f7-43c3-8914-d1c4290f6670%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20and%20several%20other%20US%20tech%20companies%20have%20tightened%20personnel%20screening.%20Some%20startups%20are%20turning%20to%20third-party%20tools%20like%20Strider%20Technologies%2C%20which%20scours%20public%20data%20to%20investigate%20individuals'%20connections%20to%20%26quot%3Bstate-sponsored%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Strider's%20website%20puts%20it.%20If%20a%20current%20or%20prospective%20employee%20is%20flagged%20by%20Strider's%20AI%2C%20FT%20reported%20that%20its%20%26quot%3Bdue%20diligence%26quot%3B%20process%20will%20then%20investigate%20their%20%26quot%3Bfamily%20or%20financial%20links%20abroad%20as%20well%20as%20their%20travel%20history.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Google%20said%20they%20hadn't%20stepped%20up%20their%20screening%20processes%20and%20told%20me%20that%20the%20company%20has%20%26quot%3Bstrict%20safeguards%26quot%3B%20for%20preventing%20the%20theft%20of%20trade%20secrets%2C%20%26quot%3Bnone%20of%20which%20are%20based%20on%20employees'%20nationality.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20members%20of%20the%20Chinese%20diaspora%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20are%20feeling%20the%20strain%20and%20paranoia%20of%20geopolitical%20tensions%20pressing%20on%20their%20social%20and%20professional%20lives.%20One%2026-year-old%20woman%20who%20works%20at%20a%20San%20Francisco%20startup%20said%20she%20was%20once%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bhoneypot%26quot%3B%20by%20a%20dance%20partner%20at%20a%20local%20bar.%20%26quot%3BHe%20told%20me%20he%20worked%20on%20a%20nuclear-related%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20like%2C%20'I%20cannot%20share%20anything%20with%20you.%20Are%20you%20looking%20at%20my%20phone%3F%20You%20don't%20seem%20like%20a%20honeypot%2C%20but%20I%20have%20to%20be%20careful%20given%20that%20you're%20a%20Chinese%20national.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20tech%20worker%2C%20she%20has%20turned%20down%20AI-related%20job%20opportunities%20to%20avoid%20scrutiny%20for%20herself%20and%20her%20family%20from%20both%20the%20US%20and%20Chinese%20governments.%20She%20also%20tries%20to%20downplay%20her%20Chinese%20accent%20and%20cultural%20identity.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20Chinese%20nationals%20don't%20agree%20with%20the%20Chinese%20government%26quot%3B%20on%20issues%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-committing-crimes-against-humanity-against-uighurs-in-xinjiang-hrw-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUyghur%20repression%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Xinjiang%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20in%20social%20situations%2C%20you%20have%20to%20vocalize%20it%20passionately%20just%20to%20lower%20the%20guard%20people%20have%20toward%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20affirmed%20this%20sentiment.%20She%20hoped%20to%20contribute%20to%20global%20AI%20safety%20work%20by%20bridging%20the%20information%20gap%20between%20Chinese-%20and%20English-language%20researchers%20and%20policymakers%2C%20but%20the%20hawkish%20environment%20has%20made