2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20TechCrunch%20journalist%20Rita%20Liao%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chinatalk.media%2Fp%2Fhow-my-china-tech-beat-fell-apart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20Chinese%20company%20refused%20her%20coverage%20because%20her%20byline%20made%20them%20look%20%26quot%3Btoo%20Chinese.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20another%20Chinese%20founder%20told%20her%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20work%20for%20no%20government.%20We%20just%20want%20to%20build%20businesses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20people%20I%20spoke%20with%20described%20their%20situation%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdouble%20bind.%26quot%3B%20On%20one%20hand%2C%20they%20came%20to%20the%20US%20to%20pursue%20opportunities%20and%20liberties%20that%20Chinese%20society%20didn't%20afford%20them.%20But%20these%20days%2C%20eerily%20similar%20state%20and%20social%20sanctions%20are%20intruding%20on%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20tensions%20are%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20people%20from%20China%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20US.%20Ordinarily%2C%20foreign%20workers%20on%20visas%20who%20temporarily%20leave%20the%20US%20must%20get%20a%20stamp%20from%20a%20local%20US%20consulate%20before%20reentering.%20But%20more%20tech%20workers%20are%20being%20put%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F2001-2009.state.gov%2Fr%2Fpa%2Fprs%2Fps%2F2005%2F42212.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextra%20processing%3C%2Fa%3E%20required%20for%20people%20working%20in%20sensitive%20industries%20before%20they%20can%20reenter%20the%20US%2C%20resulting%20in%20some%20people%20getting%20stranded%20abroad%20for%20months%20or%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20forums%20for%20Chinese%20nationals%2C%20anxious%20students%20and%20professionals%20fret%20about%20how%20to%20avoid%20extended%20processing.%20%26quot%3BI%20work%20as%20a%20machine%20learning%20engineer%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20one%20post%20from%20October.%20%26quot%3BI%20work%20on%20some%20AI%20product%20applications%20and%20do%20no%20core%20AI%20research.%20I%20thought%20that%20'sensitive%20fields'%20referred%20to%20advanced%20defense%20research%2C%20but%20now%20I%20heard%20that%20any%20STEM%20field%20can%20be%20subject%20to%20checks.%20I'm%20feeling%20panicked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlucky%20visa%20holders%20who%20get%20flagged%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20appeal%20for%20an%20extended%20leave%20of%20absence%20from%20their%20university%20or%20workplace.%20One%20AI%20Ph.D.%20student%20wrote%20in%20November%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20now%20waited%20for%20more%20than%20130%20days.%20My%20school%20has%20deferred%20me%20for%20one%20semester%2C%20but%20I%20cannot%20defer%20it%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20tensions%20ramp%20up%2C%20many%20Chinese%20tech%20workers%20are%20reconsidering%20whether%20the%20American%20dream%20is%20worth%20the%20risk.%20When%20Microsoft%20offered%20its%20China-based%20employees%20a%20chance%20to%20relocate%20to%20another%20country%2C%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20made%20some%20reluctant%20to%20take%20the%20offer%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frestofworld.org%2F2024%2Fmicrosoft-china-ai-engineer-relocation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereporting%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Rest%20of%20World%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3EGoing%20viral%20on%20X%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20tipping%20point%20for%20Sarah.%20She%20returned%20to%20China%20in%20December.%20%26quot%3BInitially%20I%20was%20afraid%20of%20trouble%20on%20the%20Chinese%20side%2C%20but%20it%20turns%20out%20that%20the%20other%20side%20is%20more%20problematic%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20about%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20faces%20a%20critical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-job-market-to-grow-2025-employers-hiring-talent-tech-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalent%20shortage%20in%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freports.nscai.gov%2Ffinal-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20National%20Security%20Commission%20on%20AI%20found%20that%20the%20number%20of%20US-born%20STEM%20and%20AI%20doctorates%20is%20not%20nearly%20keeping%20pace%20with%20the%20industry's%20growth.%20While%2042%25%20of%20top-tier%20AI%20researchers%20worked%20in%20the%20US%20in%202022%2C%20only%2018%25%20of%20them%20received%20their%20undergraduate%20degree%20here%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmacropolo.org%2Finteractive%2Fdigital-projects%2Fthe-global-ai-talent-tracker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMacro%20Polo's%3C%2Fa%3E%20AI%20Talent%20Tracker%20found.%20China%20is%20currently%20the%20largest%20source%20of%20these%20top-tier%20researchers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20are%20choosing%20to%20stay%20in%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20our%20lifetime%2C%20the%20United%20States%20risks%20losing%20the%20competition%20for%20talent%20on%20the%20scientific%20frontiers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20NSCAI%20report%20says.%20%26quot%3BImmigration%20reform%20is%20a%20national%20security%20imperative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDivyansh%20Kaushik%2C%20a%20tech%20and%20national%20security%20expert%20at%20Beacon%20Global%20Strategies%2C%20told%20me%20that%20America%20needs%20policies%20that%20are%20a%20%26quot%3Bscalpel%2C%20not%20a%20sledgehammer.%26quot%3B%20He%20recognizes%20the%20risk%20of%20espionage%2C%20citing%20China's%202017%20National%20Intelligence%20Law%2C%20which%20legally%20obligates%20all%20Chinese%20citizens%20to%20%26quot%3Bsupport%2C%20assist%2C%20and%20cooperate%20with%20state%20intelligence%20work.%26quot%3B%20But%20Kaushik%20considers%20blanket%20bans%20on%20foreign%20nationals%20just%20as%20counterproductive.%20He%20instead%20pointed%20to%20policies%20that%20restrict%20students%20from%20specific%20Chinese-military-affiliated%20universities%20from%20obtaining%20visas.%20%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20false%20positives%20and%20false%20negatives%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20US%20can%20mitigate%20the%20risk%20without%20overreaching%2C%20he%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20experts%20believe%20that%20nationality-based%20anti-espionage%20efforts%20are%20more%20security%20theater%20than%20reality.%20Yangyang%20Cheng%2C%20a%20physicist%20and%20China%20researcher%20at%20Yale%20Law%20School%2C%20told%20me%20that%20AI%20risks%20%26quot%3Bare%20not%20exclusive%20to%20Chinese%20firms%20or%20unique%20products%20of%20the%20Chinese%20authoritarian%20system.%26quot%3B%20She%20cited%20examples%20of%20American%20professors%20who%20helped%20build%20biometric%20technologies%20for%20ethnic%20oppression%20in%20Xinjiang%2C%20arguing%20that%20we%20should%20be%20focused%20on%20preventing%20harm%20wherever%20it%20originates.%20She%20thinks%20the%20TikTok%20ban%20makes%20the%20same%20mistakes.%20%26quot%3BThe%20focus%20on%20the%20Chinese%20government's%20subpoena%20power%20overlooks%20the%20many%20ways%20American%20companies%20cooperate%20with%20the%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20wrote%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fchina-espionage-tiktok-spying-national-security%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWired%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20what%20stance%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20take.%20Some%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20are%20hopeful%20that%20the%20president-elect%20will%20expand%20the%20visa%20program%20for%20high-skilled%20immigrants.%20During%20a%20recent%20intra-Republican%20fight%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-bros-debating-maga-fans-over-h-1b-visas-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EH-1B%20visas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Trump%20aligned%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%