Ministry%20to%20prosecute%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20in%20the%20alleged%20liquor%20scam.%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20released%20its%20second%20list%20of%20candidates%2C%20and%20as%20the%20deadline%20for%20nominations%20approaches%2C%20candidates%20from%20all%20parties%20are%20filing%20their%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20it's%20a%20fight%20for%20survival%3B%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20it's%20about%20prestige%2C%20and%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20it's%20about%20relevance.%20Will%20the%20AAP%20score%20a%20hat%20trick%2C%20or%20will%20a%20rejuvenated%20Congress%20spoil%20its%20chances%3F%20Can%20the%20BJP%20make%20a%20comeback%20after%20a%20gap%20of%20almost%2027%20years%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress%20have%20been%20engaged%20in%20a%20war%20of%20words%20in%20Delhi%20since%20contesting%20as%20allies%20in%20the%20June%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20While%20Ajay%20Maken%20called%20Kejriwal%20%E2%80%9Canti-national%E2%80%9D%2C%20Sandeep%20Dikshit%20has%20been%20fielded%20against%20the%20former%20chief%20minister%20from%20the%20New%20Delhi%20seat.%20Dikshit%20has%20ramped%20up%20his%20attacks%20on%20the%20AAP%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20recover%20lost%20ground.%20In%20response%2C%20the%20AAP%20has%20called%20for%20the%20Congress's%20removal%20from%20the%20INDIA%20bloc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Jugalbandi'%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20attacked%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20claiming%20that%20Kejriwal's%20campaigning%20style%20mirrored%20that%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20He%20accused%20the%20AAP%20of%20making%20false%20promises%20and%20blamed%20it%20for%20rising%20pollution%20and%20inflation.%20Kejriwal%20quickly%20responded%2C%20accusing%20Gandhi%20of%20abusing%20him.%20He%20claimed%20that%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20were%20working%20in%20tandem%20and%20that%20the%20elections%20would%20expose%20their%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ejugalbandi%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%20(duet).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AAP%20has%20grown%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20Congress%20and%20other%20parties%2C%20particularly%20among%20Purvanchalis%2C%20the%20poor%20and%20lower%20socio-economic%20classes%2C%20minorities%2C%20and%20Dalits.%20Therefore%2C%20any%20gain%20for%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%20vote%20share%20is%20likely%20to%20come%20at%20the%20AAP's%20expense.%20In%20the%202008%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20recorded%20a%2040%25%20vote%20share%2C%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20and%20Others%20getting%2036%25%2C14%25%2C%20and%2010%25%20votes%2C%20respectively.%20In%20the%20next%20state%20elections%20in%202015%2C%20the%20AAP%20secured%2054%25%20votes%20and%20the%20BJP%20got%2032%25%2C%20while%20the%20Congress%20and%20Others%20got%2010%25%20and%204%25%20votes%2C%20respectively.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Congress's%20vote%20share%20further%20declined%20to%204%25.%20Almost%20the%20entire%20vote%20chunk%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20Others%20has%20been%20absorbed%20by%20AAP%20in%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOverlapping%20Vote%20Bases%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20whenever%20the%20Congress%20has%20improved%20its%20vote%20share%20in%20local%20body%20or%20general%20elections%2C%20it%20has%20been%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20AAP.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20the%202017%20MCD%20elections%2C%20the%20AAP%20couldn't%20win%20as%20the%20Congress%20recorded%20a%2021%25%20vote%20share%E2%80%94an%2011%20percentage%20point%20(pp)%20gain%20compared%20to%20the%202015%20assembly%20polls.%20Similarly%2C%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20the%20AAP%20lost%2036%25%20of%20its%20vote%20share%20as%20the%20Congress%20saw%20a%2013%20pp%20gain%20and%20the%20BJP%2025%20pp%2C%20compared%20to%20the%202015%20assembly%20elections.%20These%20AAP%20voters%20who%20shifted%20to%20the%20BJP%20may%20have%20been%20motivated%20by%20a%20preference%20for%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20in%20the%20assembly%20and%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20AAP%20voters%20who%20shifted%20to%20the%20Congress%20may%20have%20been%20anti-BJP%20voters%2C%20backing%20Kejriwal%20in%20the%20assembly%20and%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20as%20both%20were%20seen%20as%20better%20positioned%20to%20defeat%20the%20BJP%20in%20their%20respective%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202020%20Delhi%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20AAP%20secured%2054%25%20of%20the%20vote%20share%2C%20the%20BJP%20got%2039%25%2C%20the%20Congress%204%25%2C%20and%20Others%203%25.%20Both%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP%20lost%20around%2018%25%20of%20their%20votes%20compared%20to%20the%202019%20general%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202022%20MCD%20elections%2C%20the%20AAP%20lost%2012%25%20of%20its%20vote%20share%20as%20the%20Congress%20gained%208%25%2C%20compared%20to%20the%202020%20assembly%20elections.%20The%20AAP%20won%20the%20close%20contest%20with%20134%20out%20of%20250%20seats%2C%20just%20eight%20more%20than%20the%20simple%20majority%20of%20126.%20This%20was%20an%20election%20the%20AAP%20was%20expected%20to%20win%20comfortably%20as%20the%20BJP%20was%20battling%20a%2015-year%20anti-incumbency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20the%20BJP%20bagged%2054%25%20votes%2C%20the%20AAP%2024%25%2C%20the%20Congress%2018%25%2C%20and%20Others%204%25%2C%20with%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress%20contesting%20as%20allies.%20According%20to%20trends%20from%20the%20past%20two%20election%20cycles%20(2014-15%20and%202019-20)%2C%20a%20section%20of%20voters%20swing%20between%20AAP-BJP%20and%20AAP-Congress%20from%20one%20election%20to%20the%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20Swing%20Voters%20Swing%20Again%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AAP%20holds%20a%2015%25%20lead%20over%20the%20BJP%20in%20assembly%20elections%2C%20a%20significant%20margin%20that%20is%20difficult%20to%20overcome.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%2010%20to%2015%25%20of%20AAP's%20swing%20voters%2C%20who%20Kejriwal%20hopes%20will%20shift%20back%20to%20the%20AAP%20in%20the%202025%20state%20elections.%20In%20the%202024%20general%20election%2C%20the%20Congress%20secured%2020%25%20of%20Dalit%20and%2034%25%20of%20Muslim%20support%2C%20according%20to%20CSDS%20post-poll%20data%2C%20translating%20to%20an%208%25%20vote%20share%20from%20these%20two%20communities.%20The%20BJP%20needs%20the%20Congress%20to%20retain%20some%20of%20these%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AAP's%2015%25%20lead%20in%202020%20can%20be%20broken%20down%20as%20follows%3A%203%25%20votes%20from%20Hindus%2C%202%25%20from%20Sikhs%2C%20and%2010%25%20from%20Muslims.%20The%20BJP%20led%20among%20upper%20castes%20and%20upper%20OBCs%20by%2010%25%2C%20while%20the%20AAP%20led%20among%20Dalits%20by%2030%25%2C%20Sikhs%20by%2040%25%2C%20and%20Muslims%20by%2080%25.%20The%20AAP's%20significant%20lead%20among%20Dalits%20and%20minorities%20gives%20it%20a%20real%20advantage%20over%20the%20BJP.%20In%202020%2C%20Congress%20received%2013%25%20of%20the%20Muslim%20vote%20and%204%25%20of%20the%20Sikh%20vote%2C%20according%20to%20CSDS%20post-poll%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Sticky%20Situation%20For%20Congress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20hopes%20the%20Congress%20can%20regain%20some%20of%20its%20appeal%20among%20minority%20voters%2C%20who%20may%20feel%20uneasy%20with%20the%20AAP's%20soft%20Hindutva%20approach.%20If%20the%20Congress%20were%20to%20gain%2015%25%20more%20support%20from%20Muslims%2C%20Dalits%2C%20and%20Sikhs%20compared%20to%202020%2C%20it%20could%20reduce%20the%20AAP's%20vote%20share%20by%20around%205%25%2C%20given%20that%20these%20communities%20make%20up%2035%25%20of%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20BJP%20also%20manages%20to%20capture%205%25%20of%20AAP's%20vote%20share%20due%20to%20anti-incumbency%20and%20middle-class%20disillusionment%20with%20the%20AAP%E2%80%94par